                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6251: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Leopoldville</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mallon</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-30T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 30, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Consulate at Dakar reports that fighting has taken place in Gabon and that
                    airplanes and infantry officers have been sent there as reinforcements. Please
                    comment briefly by telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
